Aim:
To write a C++ program that prints all even numbers between 1 and 100.

Algorithm:
Start
Repeat i = 1 to 100
If i % 2 == 0 → print i
Continue loop
Stop

Program:
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int main(){
    for(int i = 1; i <= 100; i++){
        if(i % 2 == 0)
            cout<<i<<" ";
    }
    return 0;
}

Sample Output:
2 4 6 8 … 100

Result:
The program successfully prints all even integers from 1 to 100.
